pendent |date=25 July 2017 |accessdate=25 July 2017}}</ref><br />{{flagicon image|Flag of YB\u015e.svg|border=no}} [[Sinjar Resistance Units]]<ref name=sinjar>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sengals-yjs-heading-for-al-raqqa-to-liberate-yazidi-women/|title=\u015eengal's YJ\u015e: heading for al-Raqqa to liberate Yazidi women|publisher=Hawar News Agency|date=3 July 2017|access-date=2017-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806191642/http://en.hawarnews.com/sengals-yjs-heading-for-al-raqqa-to-liberate-yazidi-women/|archive-date=2017-08-06|url-status=dead}}</ref><br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Sinjar Womens Units.svg|border=no}} [[\u00caz\u00eedxan Women's Units]]<ref name=sinjar/><br />{{flagicon image|Seal of Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve.svg|border=no}} '''[[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF\u2013OIR]]'''\n* {{flag|United States}}\n* {{flag|France}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/kurdish-arab-forces-syria-gains-raqqa-province/3646230.html|title=Kurdish-Arab Forces in Syria Make Gains in Raqqa Province|publisher=[[Voice of America]]|author=Sirwan Kajjo|date=21 December 2016}}</ref>\n* {{flag|United Kingdom}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/12/25/operation-raqqa-british-raf-pilots-switch-bombing-raids-heart/|title=Operation Raqqa: British RAF pilots to switch bombing raids to 'the heart' of Isil|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|author=Steven Swinford|date=25 December 2016|accessdate=16 January 2017}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Germany}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tagesschau.de/ausland/luftangriffe-syrien-aufklaerungsbilder-bundeswehr-101.html|title=Zivile Opfer in Syrien. Bundeswehr in verheerenden Luftschlag involviert|publisher=[[Tagesschau (Germany)]]|author1=Volkmar Kabisch|author2=Reiko Pinkert|language=German|date=29 March 2017|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref>\n| combatant2  = '''{{flagcountry|Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant}}'''\n| commander1  = 